<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-14T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/825b</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-14T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>323. For <persName corresp="#p_WB1">Whitlock</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>:</p>
                        <p>Respect to your telegram No. 153 of 9th. There is every sympathy and
                            desire here to assist the Belgians. Every priority has and will be given
                            and the Government is now enlarging its assistance in food relief and
                            clothing to a very remarkable degree considering the sacrifice in
                            shipping that it entails. Assistance in tools and machinery can only be
                            extended after we have accurate knowledge of what is required, a thing
                            impossible until evacuation; and credits must be established to pay
                            therefor which also must either be arranged through banks or new
                            legislation by Congress. The President has asked me to take charge of
                            organizing American interest in Belgian reconstruction and I will arrive
                            in Brussels for consultation about December 10.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>